<div class="tribe-manual">
  <ManualHeader />

  <ManualPageNav @activePage="prerequisites" />

  <div class="container pb-5">

    <div class="steps-container mb-5">

      {{!-- Step 1: Install Git --}}
      <div class="step-card" data-step-name="Install Git">
        <div class="step-header" onclick="toggleStep(this)">
          <span class="step-badge">1</span>
          <span class="step-title">Install Git</span>
          <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down step-chevron"></i>
        </div>
        <div class="step-body">
          <p>Git is the version control system used across all Tribe repositories. Install it for your operating system.</p>

          <div class="row g-3">
            <div class="col-md-4">
              <div class="card method-item h-100">
                <div class="card-body">
                  <h6><strong>macOS</strong></h6>
                  <p class="small text-muted mb-2">Install via Homebrew or Xcode Command Line Tools:</p>
                  <div class="command-block">
                    <button class="btn btn-sm copy-btn-block" onclick="copyCmd('brew install git', this)">Copy</button>
                    <code>brew install git</code>
                  </div>
                  <p class="small text-muted mt-2 mb-0">Or run <code>xcode-select --install</code> which includes Git.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-4">
              <div class="card method-item h-100">
                <div class="card-body">
                  <h6><strong>Windows</strong></h6>
                  <p class="small text-muted mb-2">Download the official installer:</p>
                  <a href="https://git-scm.com/download/win" target="_blank" class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-dark">Download Git for Windows</a>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-4">
              <div class="card method-item h-100">
                <div class="card-body">
                  <h6><strong>Linux (Ubuntu/Debian)</strong></h6>
                  <div class="command-block">
                    <button class="btn btn-sm copy-btn-block" onclick="copyCmd('sudo apt update &amp;&amp; sudo apt install git', this)">Copy</button>
                    <code>sudo apt update &amp;&amp; sudo apt install git</code>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <p class="mt-3 mb-1">Verify installation:</p>
          <div class="command-block">
            <button class="btn btn-sm copy-btn-block" onclick="copyCmd('git --version', this)">Copy</button>
            <code>git --version</code>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      {{!-- Step 2: Install Sublime Text --}}
      <div class="step-card" data-step-name="Install Sublime Text">
        <div class="step-header" onclick="toggleStep(this)">
          <span class="step-badge">2</span>
          <span class="step-title">Install Sublime Text</span>
          <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down step-chevron"></i>
        </div>
        <div class="step-body">
          <p>Sublime Text is a fast, lightweight code editor recommended for editing Tribe project files.</p>
          <div class="text-center my-3">
            <a href="https://www.sublimetext.com/" target="_blank" class="btn btn-dark btn-lg">
              <i class="fa-solid fa-download me-2"></i>Download Sublime Text
            </a>
          </div>
          <p class="small text-muted">Available for macOS, Windows, and Linux. After downloading, follow the installer instructions for your platform.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      {{!-- Step 3: Install Sublime Merge --}}
      <div class="step-card" data-step-name="Install Sublime Merge">
        <div class="step-header" onclick="toggleStep(this)">
          <span class="step-badge">3</span>
          <span class="step-title">Install Sublime Merge</span>
          <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down step-chevron"></i>
        </div>
        <div class="step-body">
          <p>Sublime Merge is a Git client by the same team behind Sublime Text. It provides a clean visual interface for Git operations like commits, merges, and diffs.</p>
          <div class="text-center my-3">
            <a href="https://www.sublimemerge.com/" target="_blank" class="btn btn-dark btn-lg">
              <i class="fa-solid fa-download me-2"></i>Download Sublime Merge
            </a>
          </div>
          <p class="small text-muted">Available for macOS, Windows, and Linux.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      {{!-- Step 4: macOS & Git Configuration --}}
      <div class="step-card" data-step-name="macOS and Git Configuration show hidden files credential manager post buffer">
        <div class="step-header" onclick="toggleStep(this)">
          <span class="step-badge">4</span>
          <span class="step-title">macOS &amp; Git Configuration</span>
          <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down step-chevron"></i>
        </div>
        <div class="step-body">
          <p>Run the following commands to configure your development environment. These are especially important on macOS but the Git configurations apply to all platforms.</p>

          <h6 class="mt-3 mb-2">Show hidden files in Finder (macOS)</h6>
          <p class="small text-muted">This makes files like <code>.env</code>, <code>.gitignore</code>, etc. visible in Finder.</p>
          <div class="command-block">
            <button class="btn btn-sm copy-btn-block" onclick="copyCmd('defaults write com.apple.finder AppleShowAllFiles TRUE; killall Finder', this)">Copy</button>
            <code>defaults write com.apple.finder AppleShowAllFiles TRUE; killall Finder</code>
          </div>

          <h6 class="mt-4 mb-2">Increase Git HTTP buffer size</h6>
          <p class="small text-muted">Prevents errors when pushing/pulling large repositories.</p>
          <div class="command-block">
            <button class="btn btn-sm copy-btn-block" onclick="copyCmd('git config --global http.postBuffer 524288000', this)">Copy</button>
            <code>git config --global http.postBuffer 524288000</code>
          </div>

          <h6 class="mt-4 mb-2">Install Git Credential Manager (macOS via Homebrew)</h6>
          <p class="small text-muted">Securely stores your Git credentials so you don't have to re-enter them.</p>
          <div class="command-block">
            <button class="btn btn-sm copy-btn-block" onclick="copyCmd('brew install --cask git-credential-manager', this)">Copy</button>
            <code>brew install --cask git-credential-manager</code>
          </div>

          <h6 class="mt-4 mb-2">Set Git to use Credential Manager</h6>
          <div class="command-block">
            <button class="btn btn-sm copy-btn-block" onclick="copyCmd('git config --global credential.helper manager', this)">Copy</button>
            <code>git config --global credential.helper manager</code>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      {{!-- Step 5: GitHub Personal Access Token --}}
      <div class="step-card" data-step-name="GitHub Personal Access Token password authentication PAT">
        <div class="step-header" onclick="toggleStep(this)">
          <span class="step-badge">5</span>
          <span class="step-title">GitHub Personal Access Token</span>
          <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down step-chevron"></i>
        </div>
        <div class="step-body">
          <p>GitHub no longer accepts account passwords for Git operations. You need a Personal Access Token (PAT) instead. When Git asks for your password, use this token.</p>

          <h6 class="mt-3 mb-2">How to generate a Personal Access Token:</h6>
          <ol>
            <li>Go to <a href="https://github.com/settings/tokens" target="_blank">github.com/settings/tokens</a></li>
            <li>Click <strong>Generate new token</strong> &rarr; <strong>Generate new token (classic)</strong></li>
            <li>Give it a descriptive name (e.g., "Tribe Development")</li>
            <li>Set an expiration (or choose "No expiration" for convenience)</li>
            <li>Select scopes: at minimum check <strong>repo</strong> (full control of private repositories)</li>
            <li>Click <strong>Generate token</strong></li>
            <li>Copy the token immediately &mdash; you won't be able to see it again</li>
          </ol>

          <div class="alert alert-warning mt-3 mb-0">
            <strong>Important:</strong> When you <code>git clone</code>, <code>git push</code>, or <code>git pull</code> and are prompted for your password, paste this token instead of your GitHub password. If you've set up Git Credential Manager (Step 4), it will remember the token for you.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      {{!-- Step 6: Install Docker --}}
      <div class="step-card" data-step-name="Install Docker Desktop docker-compose containers">
        <div class="step-header" onclick="toggleStep(this)">
          <span class="step-badge">6</span>
          <span class="step-title">Install Docker</span>
          <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down step-chevron"></i>
        </div>
        <div class="step-body">
          <p>Docker is required to run the Tribe backend (Junction + Tribe API). Install Docker Desktop for your operating system.</p>

          <div class="text-center my-3">
            <a href="https://www.docker.com/get-started/" target="_blank" class="btn btn-info btn-lg">
              <i class="fa-brands fa-docker me-2"></i>Download Docker Desktop
            </a>
          </div>

          <h6 class="mt-4 mb-2">Verify installation:</h6>
          <div class="row g-3">
            <div class="col-md-6">
              <div class="command-block">
                <button class="btn btn-sm copy-btn-block" onclick="copyCmd('docker --version', this)">Copy</button>
                <code>docker --version</code>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6">
              <div class="command-block">
                <button class="btn btn-sm copy-btn-block" onclick="copyCmd('docker compose version', this)">Copy</button>
                <code>docker compose version</code>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="alert alert-info mt-3 mb-0">
            <strong>Note:</strong> Docker Desktop for Windows and macOS includes Docker Compose by default. On Linux, you may need to install Docker Compose separately via <a href="https://docs.docker.com/compose/install/" target="_blank">docs.docker.com/compose/install</a>.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      {{!-- Step 7: Install NVM, Node.js, and npm --}}
      <div class="step-card" data-step-name="Install NVM Node.js npm nvm node version manager">
        <div class="step-header" onclick="toggleStep(this)">
          <span class="step-badge">7</span>
          <span class="step-title">Install NVM, Node.js &amp; npm</span>
          <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down step-chevron"></i>
        </div>
        <div class="step-body">
          <p>NVM (Node Version Manager) lets you install and switch between Node.js versions. Tribe's frontend requires Node.js (latest LTS) and npm.</p>

          <h6 class="mt-3 mb-2">Install NVM (macOS / Linux)</h6>
          <div class="command-block">
            <button class="btn btn-sm copy-btn-block" onclick="copyCmd('curl -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nvm-sh/nvm/v0.40.1/install.sh | bash', this)">Copy</button>
            <code><span class="comment"># Install NVM</span><br>curl -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nvm-sh/nvm/v0.40.1/install.sh | bash</code>
          </div>
          <p class="small text-muted">For Windows, use <a href="https://github.com/coreybutler/nvm-windows" target="_blank">nvm-windows</a> instead.</p>

          <h6 class="mt-4 mb-2">Restart your terminal, then install Node.js</h6>
          <div class="command-block">
            <button class="btn btn-sm copy-btn-block" onclick="copyCmd('nvm install --lts\nnvm use --lts', this)">Copy</button>
            <code><span class="comment"># Install latest LTS version of Node.js</span><br>nvm install --lts<br>nvm use --lts</code>
          </div>

          <h6 class="mt-4 mb-2">Verify installation</h6>
          <div class="command-block">
            <button class="btn btn-sm copy-btn-block" onclick="copyCmd('node --version\nnpm --version', this)">Copy</button>
            <code>node --version<br>npm --version</code>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      {{!-- Step 8: Install EmberJS --}}
      <div class="step-card" data-step-name="Install EmberJS Ember CLI ember-cli frontend framework">
        <div class="step-header" onclick="toggleStep(this)">
          <span class="step-badge">8</span>
          <span class="step-title">Install EmberJS</span>
          <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down step-chevron"></i>
        </div>
        <div class="step-body">
          <p>Ember.js is the frontend framework used by Tribe. Install the Ember CLI globally so you can create and serve Ember applications.</p>

          <div class="command-block">
            <button class="btn btn-sm copy-btn-block" onclick="copyCmd('npm install -g ember-cli', this)">Copy</button>
            <code>npm install -g ember-cli</code>
          </div>

          <h6 class="mt-4 mb-2">Verify installation</h6>
          <div class="command-block">
            <button class="btn btn-sm copy-btn-block" onclick="copyCmd('ember --version', this)">Copy</button>
            <code>ember --version</code>
          </div>

          <div class="alert alert-info mt-3 mb-0">
            <strong>Compatibility:</strong> Tribe requires Ember.js v6.0 or above and Ember CLI v6.0 or above. To learn more about EmberJS visit <a href="https://emberjs.com" target="_blank">emberjs.com</a>.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>

    <ManualFooter />

  </div>
</div>

<ManualScripts />
